In his Fourth of July address, President Biden spoke about the significance of Independence Day and the ongoing progress and challenges faced by the United States. He emphasized the idea of America as a work in progress and highlighted the core belief that all people are created equal. He acknowledged the setbacks and crises the nation has faced throughout history but expressed confidence in the country's ability to overcome them. President Biden discussed the current state of the economy, the ongoing battle for democracy and freedom, and the need for unity and hard work to ensure a better future. He also recognized the military families and service members and announced upcoming awards for their bravery and service. The President expressed optimism for the future of America and concluded by wishing everyone a happy Fourth of July and calling for a principled patriotism to protect and improve the nation.